key to our apartment.

236
00:12:23,439 --> 00:12:27,876
Step two: Enter our apartment.
Step three....

237
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,033
Enter my bedroom.

238
00:12:30,439 --> 00:12:32,828
SHELDON: Step four--
-Yeah. hang on. getting another call.

239
00:12:32,999 --> 00:12:34,432
No!

240
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:37,717
Let me tell you something. Personal
robots cannot get here soon enough.

241
00:12:41,159 --> 00:12:44,834
And that bright little star
peeking her head out early today...

242
00:12:44,999 --> 00:12:46,910
...that's Venus.

243
00:12:47,079 --> 00:12:48,353
That is so cool.

244
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,433
You know a lot about space.

245
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:56,517
Come on. When you were on TV in Fireﬂy.
you were actually in space.

246
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,111
You're not one of those guys
who believe that?

247
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:02,917
You mean one of the hopeless geeks?
No.

248
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,433
Those are crazy people.

249
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,750
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

250
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:10,632
Howard. be a dear
and get me another one of these.

251
00:13:15,719 --> 00:13:18,108
Now him. he's one of those geeks.

252
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:22,068
All right. now before you enter
my bedroom unescorted...

253
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:25,232
...I need you to understand
that this one time grant of access...

254
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:28,392
...does not create a permanent easement.

255
00:13:29,079 --> 00:13:30,148
Easement.

256
00:13:31,639 --> 00:13:34,631
It's a legal right of access. Good grief.

257
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:39,711
What? No. don't put me on hold. |--
Oh....

258
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:42,833
HOWARD:
Do you believe him?

259
00:13:42,999 --> 00:13:47,117
Normally around women.
he has the personality of a boiled potato.

260
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:50,431
Put one beer in him.
and he's M. Knight Charmalarmalon.

261
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:56,195
Is that what he's drinking?
It's not even real beer.

262
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,509
-What?
-Look at it.

263
00:13:58,280 --> 00:14:00,475
Non-alcoholic beer.

264
00:14:01,839 --> 00:14:03,750
-Then what's going on?
-I don't know.

265
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:06,434
Some sort of placebo effect. I guess.

266
00:14:06,999 --> 00:14:08,910
Placebo. you say.

267
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:11,036
Interesting.

268
00:14:11,199 --> 00:14:13,667
Yes. I'm still here.
Where am I going? I'm on a train.

269
00:14:13,839 --> 00:14:17,229
Now. what you'll be looking for
is a small wooden box...

270
00:14:17,399 --> 00:14:22,427
...located between a Hoberman Sphere
and a sample of quartz flecked with pyrite.

271
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,158
Hoberman Sphere.

272
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:27,676
It's a collapsible icosidodecahedron.

273
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:32,831
No. the thing with the time on it
is my alarm clock. My God.

274
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:37,357
Actually. in India.
the names of constellations are different.

275
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:42,116
Where you have the Big Dipper.
we have the Big Curry Pot.

276
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,949
You're making that up.

277
00:14:44,519 --> 00:14:46,111
You got me.

278
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,510
Now. what are you going to do with me?

279
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,476
-Raj. Look.
-Yes?

280
00:14:54,639 --> 00:14:56,436
-What am I looking at?
-You tell me.

281
00:14:56,999 --> 00:14:59,559
Non-alcoholic beer.

282
00:15:06,959 --> 00:15:10,747
Hi. I'm the small package
good things come in.

283
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:16,995
Okay. I got a box. but there's no key
in here. Just letters.

284
00:15:17,159 --> 00:15:18,672
That's the wrong box. Put it back.

285
00:15:18,839 --> 00:15:21,478
Oh. Sheldon. are these letters
from your grandmother?

286
00:15:21,639 --> 00:15:22,992
Don't read those letters.

287
00:15:23,159 --> 00:15:26,151
Oh. look. she calls you Moon Pie.
That is so cute.

288
00:15:26,319 --> 00:15:28,230
[SHRIEKING]
Put down the letters!

289
00:15:31,319 --> 00:15:32,593
Hey. Penny. It's Leonard.

290
00:15:32,759 --> 00:15:34,317
Hey. Leonard. How's the train ride?

291
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:37,790
Delightful. I don't know
what you're doing right now...

292
00:15:37,959 --> 00:15:41,235
...but there are little bubbles forming
in the corner of Sheldon's mouth.

293
00:15:41,399 --> 00:15:44,197
Okay. Yeah. I kind of crossed a line.
Put him back on.

294
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,509
Thank you.

295
00:15:46,839 --> 00:15:49,478
-|'m back.
-What up. Moon Pie?

296
00:15:49,999 --> 00:15:53,230
No one calls me Moon Pie but Meemaw.

297
00:15:54,879 --> 00:15:57,029
Hey. Penny. Leonard again.

298
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:01,956
So anyway. in the dream. you and I
were ice skating. just the two of us.

299
00:16:02,120 --> 00:16:04,190
And then I picked you up
by your ankles...

300
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:08,672
...and twirled you round and round
until your legs tore off.

301
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:13,990
I mean. I tried to stick them back on.
but before I could...

302
00:16:14,159 --> 00:16:18,675
...you turned into a giant loaf
of pumpernickel bread.

303
00:16:18,839 --> 00:16:20,238
What do you think that means?

304
00:16:21,599 --> 00:16:23,749
I really don't know.

305
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:26,239
I'll give you a little clue.

306
00:16:26,399 --> 00:16:29,675
My favorite sandwich?
Salami on pumpernickel.

307
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:31,629
Is that so?

308
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,318
Did you know the word
pumpernickel comes...

309
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:36,232
...from the German words
pumper and knickel.

310
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:38,630
Which loosely translates to fart goblin?

311
00:16:40,439 --> 00:16:43,237
No. I didn't.

312
00:16:45,999 --> 00:16:47,876
Okay. I found the box. Now what?

313
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:53,319
You're holding a Japanese puzzle box.
which takes 10 precise moves to open.

314
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:56,552
Okay. first locate the
panel with the diamond pattern...

315
00:16:56,720 --> 00:17:00,269
...and slide the center portion
1 millimeter to the left.

316
00:17:00,439 --> 00:17:02,430
Then. on the opposite end of the box...

317
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:05,592
...slide the entire panel
down 2 millimeters.

318
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,557
You'll hear a slight click.

319
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:11,235
Hang on. Sheldon. do you have
any emotional attachment to this box?

320
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:14,631
No. It's a novelty I ordered off
the Internet. Did you hear the click?

321
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,358
Not yet.

322
00:17:19,559 --> 00:17:21,231
There it is.

323
00:17:24,559 --> 00:17:25,958
Okay. here's another one.

324
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:29,954
If you married the famous rock guitarist
Johnny Winter...

325
00:17:30,119 --> 00:17:32,349
...you'd be Summer Winter.

326
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,036
-Uh-huh.
-Yep.

327
00:17:36,439 --> 00:17:40,955
Okay. I'm gonna just go for broke here
and say I like you.

328
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,633
Yeah?

329
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:44,513
So here's my question:

330
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:48,832
Do you see any conversational path that
would take us from where we are now...

331
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,594
...to a place where I could ask you out
and you'd say yes?

332
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:54,679
No.

333
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:58,670
Fair enough. I'll leave you in peace.

334
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:00,398
Thank you.

335
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,670
But before I go...

336
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:09,957
...would you mind if I just take one picture
of us together for my Facebook page?

337
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:11,473
Sure.

338
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:21,798
Okay. Great.

339
00:18:21,959 --> 00:18:24,268
Can I take one
where it looks like we're making out?

340
00:18:25,799 --> 00:18:32,193
Okay. now you're going to insert
the flash drive into the USB port.

341
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:33,634
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

342
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,753
She calls me Moon Pie
because I'm nummy-nummy...

343
00:18:37,919 --> 00:18:40,433
...and she could just eat me up.

344
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:45,957
Now please put the flash drive
in the USB port.

345
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:50,319
The one that looks like
a little duck's mouth.

346
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:55,472
-Hey. how'd it go?
-Terminator broke my phone.

347
00:19:01,319 --> 00:19:03,037
Excuse me.

348
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,799
Okay. I'll be honest with you.

349
00:19:05,959 --> 00:19:09,110
I've spent the last two hours imagining
various scenarios in my head...

350
00:19:09,279 --> 00:19:11,713
...trying to come up with some line
to say to you...

351
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:14,997
...but then I finally realized
you're a human being. I'm a human being.

352
00:19:15,159 --> 00:19:16,148
I could just say--

